.TH "_cxlflash_vlun_resize" 9 "_cxlflash_vlun_resize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_cxlflash_vlun_resize \- changes the size of a virtual LUN
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _cxlflash_vlun_resize
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "struct ctx_info *ctxi "  ","
.BI "struct dk_cxlflash_resize *resize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
SCSI device associated with LUN owning virtual LUN.
.IP "ctxi" 12
Context owning resources.
.IP "resize" 12
Resize ioctl data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
On successful return, the user is informed of the new size (in blocks)
of the virtual LUN in last LBA format. When the size of the virtual
LUN is zero, the last LBA is reflected as -1. See comment in the
prologue for \fB_cxlflash_disk_release\fP regarding AFU syncs and contexts
on the error recovery list.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
